    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>
                <date>8 March 1859</date>
            </p>
            <p>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. and Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have delayed until the last moment<lb/> to write in the hope of
                having something favorable to add; but<lb/> in vain. There are two or three who
                partially promise to<lb/> become subscribers if it become a Weekly, but would like
                to<lb/> see it first and object to paying in advance.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In congregational matters<lb/> all is quiet with us, and I believe
                likewise with the others<lb/> in some degree. They are preparing for a second
                Confirmation<lb/> on <add>שבועות</add>: I send you herewith one of the
                Catechisms.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">What I have marked with <hi rend="underline">double lines</hi> is
                strongly<lb/> objected to by <persName>Pope Gerstle</persName>; but the moderator
                    <persName>Gotthelf</persName><lb/> has satisfied him that it will not do to
                slash too<lb/> deeply at first. I need not comment thereon,<lb/> and leave it
                entirely optional with you to notice the<lb/> choice morceau. Last year 15 were
                confirmed, of,<lb/> whom only <hi rend="underline">one</hi> (father and son)
                observes the <date>Sabbath</date>: so<lb/> much for consistency: and from a
                knowledge of the<lb/> parties generally, I suspect the new batch will be<lb/> the
                same. The } is mine.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I hope soon to have better news, and may<lb/> success attend you in
                all your praiseworthy exertions is<lb/> the sincere wish of<lb/> Rev<hi rend="sup"
                    >d</hi>. and Dear Sir<lb/> Truly Yours</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">A. I. H. Bernal</persName>
            </p>
            <p><persName>Mr B.</persName> and <persName>Mr &amp; Mrs Hassan</persName><lb/> present
                their best respects and<lb/> kind regards.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
